setting up mac ports:
$ sudo port install avarice avrdude avr-libc avr-gdb avr-gcc avr-binutils}

===

blinkie pin assignments
ATmega32u4		Remote
--------------------	-------------
PB3	MISO	in	nrf24L01 MISO
PB2	MOSI	out	nrf24L01 MOSI
PB1	SCK	out	nrf24L01 SCK
PB0	SS	out	nrf24L01 CSN
PB6		out	nrf24L01 CE
PB4	PCINT4	in	nrf24L01 IRQ

PC7		out	yellow debug LED
PC6	OC3A	out	Green PWM throbber

PF0	ADC0	in	Vbatt
PF1	ADC1	in	Vled

PD1     SDA	i/o	LCD (must use pullups)
PD0     SCL	out	LCD (must use pullups)

PB7	OC0A	out	TLC5940 GSCLK (was going to use CLK0 on PC7 but it required a fuse reprog)
PD2	RXD1	in	TLC5940 SOUT (not really planning on using)
PD3	TXD1	out	TLC5940 SIN
PD5	XCK1	out	TLC5940 SCLK
PD4		out	TLC5940 XLAT
PD7		out	TLC5940 BLANK
		i/o	TLC5940 XERR (need pulldown?)
PD6	T1	in	TLC5940 GSCLK

TIMER0: used to generate 8 MHz clock for TLC5940 (no ints, just togle OC0A)
TIMER1: used to count up TIMER0 pulses to signal end of GS cycle (interrupt) 
TIMER3: used to drive a throbber (generate an overflow interrupt)
TIMER4: generate a 1 ms clock pulse

USART1: used as a pseudo SPI to drive TLC5940 (no interrupts, its fast)
TWI: used to talk to debug LCD (uses interrupts)
SPI: used to talk to nRF24L01 (no interrupts)

